            "items": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p class=\"text-align-center\"><em><span class=\"font-size-x-large\">SHOPPING MALL WEBQUEST</span></em></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"break text-align-center\"><em><span class=\"font-size-x-large\"> </span></em></div>\n"
                },
                {
                    "type": "image",
                    "src": "https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/userfiles/4/4a110e717b91bc323f8eb8ae5691c988.jpg",
                    "altText": "",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "scale": 1,
                    "link": ""
                }
            ],
            "sections": [
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155673"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "1. Inleiding",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p><span><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">You might recognize the picture on your right hand side. This is the 'Passage' in The Hague, the first indoor shopping centre in the world! It was built at the end of the 19<sup>th</sup> century. In those days, shopping at the \"Passage\" was just for the rich and the famous.</span></strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Nowadays, shopping malls are for everyone and it's big business - especially in the US. But also in Europe we are seeing more and more shopping malls.</span></strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">In this webquest, you will learn a lot about shopping malls. And it gets better: you will create your own shopping mall! Go to the next page for more information.</span></strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong> </strong></span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"break\"> </div>\n"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "link": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IUlDzwaBYk4",
                            "title": "Westfield mall",
                            "description": "",
                            "comment": ""
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155676"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "2. Taak",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Creating your own shopping mall is no easy task. There are many things you will have to think about. But don't worry; we will help and guide you through this process.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">At the end of this project, your group will present their shopping mall to the rest of the class. In this presentation, we want to see and hear the following \u2026</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     The name of your mall</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     A location + reasoning (why that location)</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     A poster or flyer for your mall</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     Mall directory (at least 30 shops + 2 anchor stores)</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     A 500 word essay on what makes a successful shopping</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">        mall + 3 examples of malls that fit your description  </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">        (use links!)</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     10 Shopping Mall checklists</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v     <span class=\"font-size-medium\">A presentation</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">All the above has to be presented in a 10 or 15 minute presentation - in which each group member will have to speak! You will be graded and receive a mark.</span></strong></p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155678"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "3. Werkwijze",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><strong><span><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">Visit the website of the Mall of America, the biggest shopping centre in the world. It is so big you can find a roller coaster inside! Check the link for more information on the Mall of America ...</span> <a title=\"Mall of America\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6M__CK89FhM\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">Mall of America</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\"> </span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">1. Start your research for your criteria list here. It will also give you a lot of useful background info when you start creating your own mall. Ask yourself the following question: what makes a succesful shopping mall? To get you started, look into ...</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Location</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Accessibility</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Types of shops / mall directory</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Anchor stores</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Events</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">The 'X' factor - what makes it unique?</span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><br/>\n<strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">2. Visit the 9 malls listed in 'bronnen'. Fill in the 10 checklists in the project (bijlage 1 p. 6;<span>read How</span> <span>to fill out your checklist p. 5</span> first )which was handed out.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">3. Now that you have looked at a few websites and filled in the checklists, you should have some idea of what a succesful shopping mall is. Start working on a 500 word essay on shopping malls.</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Part 1: Tell the reader what your research topic is. Also give the reader some information about how you did your actual research, who did what in your group and how did the cooperation within your group go. </span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Part 2: Inform the reader of your research results. What websites appealed to you and why? What information did you think was very important to find as a visitor? Which shopping malls did you like and which ones didn't?</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Part 3: Give us your top 3 of shopping malls and explain your choices.</span></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">4. Start creating your own shopping mall! You now have enough background information to start creating your own mall. Start with thinking of a location, target group and anchor stores. Continue with your directory - and don't forget to categorize your shops! After that, make a flyer which contains some basic information on your mall.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\" style=\"color:#000000;\">5. Now start preparing your presentation. The presentation has to be 10 - 15 minutes. You should start by telling us a bit about your group - who did what and how did that go. After that, tell the audience about your research and mall top 3. End the presentation with your own mall. Show the flyer, tell us something on your anchor stores, the location, etc.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Don't forget that the presentation will be graded!</span></strong></p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155680"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "4. Bronnen",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<h2>4. Bronnen</h2>\n<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\"><strong><em>List of malls</em></strong></span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Mall of America\" href=\"http://www.mallofamerica.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Mall of America</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"><img title=\"Metrocentre\" src=\"http://mediaprovider.kennisnet.nl/MediaProvider/img/14009423.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"203\" height=\"175\" align=\"right\"/></span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Metrocentre\" href=\"http://www.metrocentre.uk.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Metrocentre</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Westfield London\" href=\"http://uk.westfield.com/london\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Westfield London</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Victoria Square Mall\" href=\"http://www.victoriasquare.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Victoria Square Mall</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Forum Shopping Mall\" href=\"http://www.forumtheshoppingmall.com.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Forum Shopping Mall</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Eaton Centre Toronto\" href=\"http://www.torontoeatoncentre.com/en/Pages/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Eaton Centre Toronto</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\">   </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"King of Prussia\" href=\"http://www.kingofprussiamall.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">King of Prussia</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"><img title=\"Eaton Centre Toronto\" src=\"http://mediaprovider.kennisnet.nl/MediaProvider/img/14009426.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"199\" height=\"185\" align=\"right\"/></span></p>\n<p><a title=\"South Coast Plaza\" href=\"http://www.southcoastplaza.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">South Coast Plaza</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Boulevard Mall\" href=\"http://www.boulevardmall.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Boulevard Mall</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\"> </span></p>\n<p><a title=\"Willowbrook Mall\" href=\"http://www.shopwillowbrookmall.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Willowbrook Mall</span></a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\"><strong><em><span>Other useful links ...</span></em></strong></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\"><a title=\"Floorplanner\" href=\"http://nl.floorplanner.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Floorplanner</a></span></p>\n<p><a title=\"About anchor stores\" href=\"http://retail.about.com/od/glossary/g/anchor_store.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">About anchor stores</span></a></p>\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\"><a title=\"Article on&#xA0;successfull malls\" href=\"http://www.ciremagazine.com/article.php?article_id=772\" target=\"_blank\">Article on successfull malls</a></span></p>\n</div>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155682"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "5. Beoordeling",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">As said before, you will be graded (presentation) so it is very important you give this project 100%!</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Also, your other work will be graded. If the quality of your work is below par, you will be asked to redo the work.</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155684"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "6. Terugblik",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Don't forget to check your work. Make sure you have the following</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">A catching name and location for your mall</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">A brochure and flyer / poster</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">A mall directory</span></strong></li>\n<li><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">An essay and criteria list</span></strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Also, check the rubric if you want to know what you will be tested on (see beoordeling). Grammar and spelling will be important for writing exercises and pronunciation and tone will be important for speaking. Don't forget we're also looking for the X Factor - meaning that all your end products should make want to visit your mall!!</span></strong></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\">If all goes well, after this project you will have gained vital knowledge on the fascinating world of shopping malls. You will know</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<ol>\n<li><span class=\"font-size-medium\">What anchor stores are \u2026</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"font-size-medium\">How shops have to be grouped</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"font-size-medium\">What is needed for a successful mall</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"font-size-medium\">How to promote your product (your own mall in this example)</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"font-size-medium\">We hope you have enjoyed your quest!</span></p>\n</div>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "155686"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "7. Docentpagina",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<div class=\"freeformat\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">This webquest has as goal not only to acquaint students with English related to the retail business, but also to broaden their professional horizon and learn a thing or two about the retail world. More specifically, they will learn what makes a good shopping centre and what kind of shops you need.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">This is a group exercise, written for groups of three students. If a fourth student has to participate, our advice is to make him CEO. If only two students participate, our advice is to leave out the CEO.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">You should block 4 - 5 lessons, excluding presentations. If you want to incorporate lectures, we advice you to give the following lectures:</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v </span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Marketing - successful promotional materials</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v </span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Shopping malls - an introduction</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">v </span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Shopping malls - what is the X factor?</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">All information can be found in the EIW material (the books and method of 'Handel en Commercie' ROC Mondriaan)</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span><span class=\"font-size-medium\">To prevent freeloading, you are free to raise the number of points that can be earned individually. For more information on the this subject, </span><a title=\"click here\" href=\"http://www.griffith.edu.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0010/194995/AssessingGroupwork-final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"font-size-medium\">click here</span></a> <span class=\"font-size-medium\">.</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"font-size-medium\">Good luck and have fun!!</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span> </span></strong></p>\n</div>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                }
            ]
